Data Analyst

Sun Life - Toronto, ON

Job details

No matching job preferences
Salary
$53,300$86,300 a year
Job type
Fixed term contract

Full Job Description

You are as unique as your background, experience and point of view. Here, youll be encouraged, empowered and challenged to be your best self. You'll work with dynamic colleagues - experts in their fields - who are eager to share their knowledge with you. Your leaders will inspire and help you reach your potential and soar to new heights. Every day, you'll have new and exciting opportunities to make life brighter for our Clients - who are at the heart of everything we do. Discover how you can make a difference in the lives of individuals, families and communities around the world.

Job Description:

***Please note this is a contract opportunity ending Dec 27, 2024***

About the role:

Reporting to the Manager, Compliance Analytics, the Data Analyst is responsible for supporting Compliance with a variety of analytics initiatives. These responsibilities include reviewing large quantities of data for a variety of compliance functions, developing enhanced reporting, automation of various processes and performing various investigative and analytical functions.

What will you do?

  • Work with Compliance PMO to develop compliance metrics and dashboards to support effective oversight of business operations compliance with regulatory requirements and improved risk management
  • Undertake projects that relate to Compliance, Analytics and Technology
  • Design, develop and implement business requests and analytical solutions using technologies such as Excel, SAS/SQL, Python and Tableau
  • Build automations in Excel and/or other tools to support business needs
  • Produces specialized reports and data extracts for assigned business areas while demonstrating solid understanding of business objectives
  • Maintain and generate the reports and ensures the accuracy of the information
  • Produce technical and user documentation to support create tools and dashboards

What you need to succeed?

  • Bachelor degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or equivalent experience
  • At least 2 years of experience in data analytics
  • At least 2 years experience with software packages like VBA, SQL, SAS, Python
  • Knowledge of cloud platforms such as AWS
  • Experienced in data visualization tools (Tableau)
  • Experience with ETL processes, data management, and process improvement
  • Excellent programming skills with a keen aptitude for learning new programming languages and analytics tools
  • Strong problem solving and analytical skills
  • Ability to work independently as well as in a team
  • Excellent oral, written and interpersonal communication skills

Preferred Skills:

  • Insurance/Financial Services experience preferred
  • Conceptual knowledge of data science, predictive modelling is a plus

What's in it for you?

  • Remote/ Hybrid Work
  • Competitive salary and bonus structure influenced by market range data
  • A friendly, collaborative, and inclusive culture
  • Being part of our Analytics community, where we share best practices and broaden skill-sets
  • The opportunity to move along a variety of career paths with amazing networking potential
  • Access to our Global Learning Centre, available 24/7 for your learning needs
  • Wellness programs that support the three pillars of your health mental, physical and financial

The Base Pay range is for the primary location for which the job is posted. It may vary depending on the work location of the successful candidate or other factors. In addition to Base Pay, eligible Sun Life employees participate in various incentive plans, payment under which is discretionary and subject to individual and company performance. Certain sales focused roles have sales incentive plans based on individual or group sales results.

Diversity and inclusion have always been at the core of our values at Sun Life. A diverse workforce with wide perspectives and creative ideas benefits our clients, the communities where we operate and all of us as colleagues. We welcome applications from qualified individuals from all backgrounds.

Persons with disabilities who need accommodation in the application process or those needing job postings in an alternative format may e-mail a request to thebrightside@sunlife.com.

At Sun Life we strive to create a flexible work environment where our employees are empowered to do their best work. Several flexible work options are available and can be discussed throughout the selection process depending on the role requirements and individual needs.

We thank all applicants for showing an interest in this position. Only those selected for an interview will be contacted.

Salary Range:

53,300/53 300 - 86,300/86 300

Job Category:

Advanced Analytics

Posting End Date:

29/05/2023

cover_letter:
Dear Hiring Manager,

I am writing to express my interest in the Data Analyst position, and I believe my experience as a full-stack data scientist would make me a valuable asset to this role and your company. With my passion for number crunching and data visualization, I am excited to create solutions that can make a difference in the lives of individuals, families, and communities around the world.

In my current position as a Data Scientist at Hotmob Limited, I worked on several data analytics and machine learning projects to proactively derive insights from large datasets. My proudest achievement was automating the company's entire data processing system in SAS and seamlessly porting the data to the highly efficient PowerBI Dashboard, which impressed the Business Intelligence Team of Prudential HK. I believe this experience will translate well to the job as I will be required to develop automated processes and perform various analytical functions for compliance purposes.

I am confident that my skill set with programming languages like Python, SAS, SQL, and proficiency in machine learning frameworks such as Pytorch, Tensorflow, Keras, and Scikit-learn will be a valuable asset in creating analytical solutions and automating manual tasks similar to the job functions described in the Job Position Detail section. Moreover, I have vast experience in data visualization tools like Tableau, which I believe will be useful in generating specialized reports and data extracts for assigned business areas while demonstrating a solid understanding of business objectives.

Finally, I understand that the compliance sector can face significant challenges related to regulatory compliances, which requires businesses to have a proactive approach to mitigate risks associated. Therefore, I would like to highlight my experience in developing and implementing business requests and analytical solutions using Excel, SAS/SQL, Python, and Tableau.

With my background in data analysis and strong problem-solving skills, I am confident to tackle any challenges that may arise in any data-intensive project. I appreciate the opportunity to apply for this position, and I am excited to have the chance to make a difference in your company.

Thank you for considering my application.

Best regards,

Geoffrey Wong.

Indeed's salary guide

  • Not provided by employer

Full Job Description

Who needs insurance? Everybody. That keeps us busy. Very busy. At the Intact Lab, we use machine learning, data science, software engineering, AI, agility, UX and design thinking to transform the customer experience for millions of Canadians.

Join our team and get ready to explore, take risks, make mistakes, and learn all day, every day. Well support your goals with tools, opportunities, and flexibility. Its our employee promise.

Our hybrid work model preserves the balance between working from home and enjoying meaningful in-person interaction. The needs for every role are different but on average, you will be together with your colleagues at least once per week, with our leadership team in office three to four days weekly to be present for their teams.

Ready to make your mark?

About the role

Were looking for a Senior Data Analyst to join our growing team of Digital Analytics!

What youll do here:

  • Drive profitable digital growth by creating and communicating thoughtful analyses of digital acquisition or sales initiatives across multi-provincial contact centers, direct customers and brokers.
  • Perform continuous improvements of tools, data and reports developed or used by Digital Analytics team.
  • Collaborate within a high-performing, high-output team to support business partners in meeting special requests for data analysis and optimize the use of data and platforms used in the customer acquisition and digital adoption programs.


What you bring to the table:

  • Relevant college diploma or university degree or any equivalent combination of education and experience
  • A minimum of 5 years experience in a Data analysis role
  • Excellent knowledge of programming language: SQL
  • Excellent Knowledge of databases (Oracle or Snowflake)
  • Knowledge of SAS, VBA or Python an asset
  • Knowledge of Office Suite, particularly Excel, Power BI
  • Can learn/adapt quickly to a changing environment
  • Can analyze and communicate complex results
  • Strong communication skills in effectively working within a virtual team and collaborating with a number of business partners
  • Can prioritize and often meet tight deadlines
  • Bilingual (French and English) Need to interact on a regular basis with colleagues across the country

What we offer

Working here means you'll be empowered to be and do your best every day. Here is some of what you can expect as a permanent member of our team:

  • A financial rewards program that recognizes your success

  • An industry leading Employee Share Purchase Plan; we match 50% of net shares purchased

  • An extensive flex pension and benefits package, with access to virtual healthcare

  • Flexible work arrangements

  • Possibility to purchase up to 5 extra days off per year

  • An annual wellness account that promotes an active and healthy lifestyle

  • Access to tools and resources to support physical and mental health, embracing change and connecting with colleagues

  • A dynamic workplace learning ecosystem complete with learning journeys, interactive online content, and inspiring programs

  • Inclusive employee-led networks to educate, inspire, amplify voices, build relationships and provide development opportunities

  • Inspiring leaders and colleagues who will lift you up and help you grow

  • A Community Impact program, because what you care about is a part of what makes you different. And how you contribute to your community should be just as unique

We are an equal opportunity employer

At Intact, we value diversity and strive to create an inclusive, accessible workplace where all individuals feel valued, respected, and heard.

If we can provide a specific adjustment to make the recruitment process more accessible for you, please let us know when we reach out about a job opportunity. Well work with you to meet your needs.

Click here to review other important information about the hiring process, including background checks, internal candidates, and eligibility to work in Canada.

If you are an employee of Intact, belairdirect, or Johnson Insurance, please apply for this role on Contact People.

cover_letter:
Dear Hiring Manager,

I am thrilled to apply for the Senior Data Analyst position that is currently available at your organization. My name is Geoffrey Wong, and I am a full-stack data scientist with a passion for using my skills to make a positive impact on the world around me.

I understand that in today's fast-paced world, businesses need to be agile and adaptable to stay ahead of the competition. My experience working with various machine learning frameworks, including Tensorflow, Pytorch, Keras and Scikit-Learn, combined with my proficiency in programming languages such as C, JAVA, Python and SQL, make me an ideal candidate for this role. Additionally, my ability to visualize data using tools such as Tableau, Power BI and LookerStudio, allows me to present insights efficiently, in a way that is easily understandable and actionable.

I see that one of the main responsibilities of the Senior Data Analyst is to communicate thoughtful analyses of digital acquisition or sales initiatives across multi-provincial contact centers, direct customers and brokers. One project that stands out is my experience training deep learning models to predict insurance fraud. I impressed the Business Intelligence Team of Prudential HK with this project and was able to revamp their entire data processing system in SAS with PowerQuery, seamlessly porting data to the highly efficient PowerBI dashboard. Additionally, I have developed two dashboards to showcase exceptional behavior in subscribed emails and browsing patterns, including web and app usage and location-based data.

I understand that digital adoption programs are constantly evolving, and businesses need to rapidly adapt to remain relevant. One problem you may face is an increase in competition from other companies that leverage AI technology to gain an edge. My experience with machine learning algorithms, combined with excellent communication skills, would allow me to develop strategies with real-time insights that will give your company a competitive advantage. 

Thank you for considering my application. I am excited about the opportunity to join your team and contribute to the success of your organization.

Sincerely,

Geoffrey Wong

Director, People Analytics

Mackenzie Financial Corporation - Toronto, ON

Job details

No matching job preferences
Job type
Full-time

Indeed's salary guide

  • Not provided by employer
  • $107K$136K a year is Indeed's estimated salary for this role in Toronto, ON.
 

Full Job Description

Job Description:
IGM Financial Inc. is one of Canada's leading diversified wealth and asset management companies with approximately $271 billion in total assets under managements. The company provides a broad range of financial planning and investment management services to help more than two million Canadians meet their financial goals. Its activities are carried out principally through IG Wealth Management and Mackenzie Investments

Under IGM Financials unique business model based on leading brands and multi-channel distribution strategy is Mackenzie Investments, founded in 1967. Mackenzie Investments is a holistic asset-management partner for thousands of Canadian financial advisors and the investors they support.

At Mackenzie Investments You Can Build Your Career with Confidence .

We have a vision and a strategy that will challenge the way business in this industry is done and help Canadians be successful in the ways that mean the most to them. As part of our team, you will do some of your best work, develop some of your most valuable skills and give back in ways that make a difference in the lives of Canadians. We are proud to be recognized as one of Canadas Top Employers by Mediacorp Canada Inc. for empowering our employees with the tools to thrive while working remotely, while also providing resources to ensure physical and mental wellness were put front and centre .

Join an unstoppable team that is embedded in continuous learning, understanding, and knowledge sharing. You will thrive in our supportive environment where you can indulge your curiosity to learn, while receiving the feedback you need to refine your skills and abilities. We are dedicated to offering a hybrid work environment when applicable.

Mackenzie Investments is a diverse workplace committed to doing business inclusively - this starts with having a representative workforce! We encourage applications from all qualified candidates that represent the diversity present across Canada including racialized persons, women, Indigenous persons, persons with disabilities, 2SLGBTQIA+ community, gender diverse and neurodiverse individuals, as well as all who may contribute to the further diversification of ideas.


What The Role Is All About

This role (COE) has the primary responsibility for IGM wide people analytics. While operational COEs continue to be responsible for their own reporting, this role will provide expertise and input on how these reporting efforts amalgamate with the overall people analytics strategy and framework. This role will ensure consistency with all reporting provided by HR across functions. Working closely with the HR Technology team, this role will also leverage technology to create reporting efficiencies. Acting as the data consultant for HR, this role supports HR teams in more complex analysis requiring information from different platforms.


Responsibilities:

  • Design and build out a data organization for HR
    • Design HR data architecture, framework and strategy through understanding current and future needs
    • Design/re-design/enhance HR data and reporting
    • Active participant in establishing data governance, operations and reporting activities
  • People Analytics
    • Create a 3-year roadmap for people analytics
    • Leverage available data science methods to establish statistical analysis to identify correlation and causation of different aspects of HR
    • Build predictive analytics
    • Bring forward new, unanticipated insights from data to help set the HR strategic direction and investment
  • Consulting / Subject Matter Expert for HR Leaders
    • Educate/develop analytics capability across HR
    • Build strong relationships and been seen as thought leader/partner to HR leaders and Centres of Expertise
    • Enhance data visualization capabilities to enable senior leaders to quickly grasp difficult concepts, identify patterns and make effective decisions
    • Support the translation of the data into actionable insights via effective data storytelling
  • Risk Analytics
    • Develop and produce ongoing risk dashboards across various business units
    • Modify risk analytics as new risks emerge
    • Support and create analytics for various senior audiences and actively work with leaders to present insights


What Are The Qualifications:

  • 7+ years of experience in a data/reporting/analytics environment.
  • Bachelors degree in a relevant business field
  • Experience in consulting firms/large organizations is preferred
  • Advanced knowledge of PowerBI, Tableau, Advanced Macro Excel, Successfactors reporting modules
  • Foundational HR knowledge including knowledge of HR business processes & HR data.
  • Consulting and communication skills with the ability to translate data into insights
  • Coaching and mentoring cross functional team members and leaders
  • Strong relationship builder with collaboration and influencing skills
  • Ability to make decisions, meet deadlines in a multi-tasking environment

Please visit our c areer page by clicking on the following link: https://www.mackenzieinvestments.com/en/careers

We thank all applicants for their interest in Mackenzie Investments; however only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.

Mackenzie Investments is an accessible employer committed to providing a barrier free recruitment experience. If you require an accommodation or this information in an alternate format at any stage of the recruitment process, please reach out to the Talent Acquisition team who will work with you to meet your needs.

Please apply by June 8, 2023.

#LI-JS2
#LI-Hybrid

You will thrive in our supportive environment where you can indulge your curiosity to learn, while receiving the feedback you need to refine your skills and abilities. We are dedicated to offering a hybrid work environment when applicable.
Mackenzie Investments is a diverse workplace committed to doing business inclusively - this starts with having a representative workforce! We encourage applications from all qualified candidates that represent the diversity present across Canada  including racialized persons, women, Indigenous persons, persons with disabilities, 2SLGBTQIA+ community, gender diverse and neurodiverse individuals, as well as all who may contribute to the further diversification of ideas.
What The Role Is All About
This role (COE) has the primary responsibility for IGM wide people analytics. While operational COEs continue to be responsible for their own reporting, this role will provide expertise and input on how these reporting efforts amalgamate with the overall people analytics strategy and framework. This role will ensure consistency with all reporting provided by HR across functions. Working closely with the HR Technology team, this role will also leverage technology to create reporting efficiencies. Acting as the data consultant for HR, this role supports HR teams in more complex analysis requiring information from different platforms.
Responsibilities:
- Design and build out a data organization for HR
- Design HR data architecture, framework and strategy through understanding current and future needs
- Design/re-design/enhance HR data and reporting
- Active participant in establishing data governance, operations and reporting activities
- People Analytics
- Create a 3-year roadmap for people analytics
- Leverage available data science methods to establish statistical analysis to identify correlation and causation of different aspects of HR
- Build predictive analytics
- Bring forward new, unanticipated insights from data to help set the HR strategic direction and investment
- Consulting / Subject Matter Expert for HR Leaders
- Educate/develop analytics capability across HR
- Build strong relationships and been seen as thought leader/partner to HR leaders and Centres of Expertise
- Enhance data visualization capabilities to enable senior leaders to quickly grasp difficult concepts, identify patterns and make effective decisions
- Support the translation of the data into actionable insights via effective data storytelling
- Risk Analytics
- Develop and produce ongoing risk dashboards across various business units
- Modify risk analytics as new risks emerge
- Support and create analytics for various senior audiences and actively work with leaders to present insights
What Are The Qualifications:
- 7+ years of experience in a data/reporting/analytics environment.
- Bachelors degree in a relevant business field
- Experience in consulting firms/large organizations is preferred
- Advanced knowledge of PowerBI, Tableau, Advanced Macro Excel, Successfactors reporting modules
- Foundational HR knowledge including knowledge of HR business processes & HR data.
- Consulting and communication skills with the ability to translate data into insights
- Coaching and mentoring cross functional team members and leaders
- Strong relationship builder with collaboration and influencing skills
- Ability to make decisions, meet deadlines in a multi-tasking environment
Please visit our c areer page by clicking on the following link: https://www.mackenzieinvestments.com/en/careers
We thank all applicants for their interest in Mackenzie Investments; however only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.
Mackenzie Investments is an accessible employer committed to providing a barrier free recruitment experience. If you require an accommodation or this information in an alternate format at any stage of the recruitment process, please reach out to the Talent Acquisition team who will work with you to meet your needs.
Please apply by June 8, 2023.

cover_letter:
Dear Hiring Manager,

I am delighted to submit my application for the Director of People Analytics role at Mackenzie Investments. With my experiences as a full-stack data scientist, I am confident that my expertise and passion would be a great addition to your team. Furthermore, I am excited about the possibility of becoming a part of a company that provides invaluable opportunities for personal growth while promoting the financial well-being of Canadians.

In my current role at HotMobile, I have been responsible for automating the company's pipeline using tools such as Airflow, while also leading projects in predictive modelling and experimentation. One project I am particularly proud of is building a web crawling tool to process URLs faster and cutting costs by 50%. Additionally, I have extensive experience with machine learning frameworks and programming languages such as Pytorch, Tensorflow, and Java, as well as experience with data visualization and Google Cloud Platform tools.

The importance of People Analytics is essential within any organization, and I believe my skill set can benefit your company's framework. I understand that merging data across functions can be a challenging task. Still, I think my experience in consolidating information, identifying patterns, and using data storytelling techniques can support your HR teams in implementing comprehensive reporting strategies. Besides, I can contribute to building scalable, efficient, and accurate data infrastructures through acquired knowledge of HR business processes and essential analytics that would open new areas of growth opportunities within the company.

Considering the rapid advancement of technology, many companies now see their competitors having an edge over them with the assistance of AI. I believe Mackenzie Investments can maintain its competitive advantage with the skillset I bring to the table. One example is the AI tool I built, which has consistently generated accurate predictive models for fraud detection, which could benefit the company's risk analytics. 

Thank you for your consideration. I look forward to discussing this position further with you.

Sincerely, 

Geoffrey Wong

Full Job Description

Position Title: Data & Analytics Operations Lead

Position Type: Regular - Full-Time

Position Location: Toronto HQ

Requisition ID: 22100


We know the importance that food plays in people's lives the power it has to bring people, families and communities together. Our purpose is to bring enjoyment to peoples lives through great tasting food, in a way which reflects our values. McCain has recently committed to implementing regenerative agriculture practices across 100 percent of our potato acreage by 2030. Ask us more about our commitment to sustainability.


OVERVIEW

Our Technology teams goal is to inspire growth through innovative technology experiences. McCain is embarking on an ambitious digital transformation across our business from Agriculture to Manufacturing to Customers and Consumers. As part of this transformation, we are making significant investments into our data systems and building digital products for our customers, key suppliers and McCain team members to enable digital processes and data-driven automation over time. Through our investments, we will transform McCain to be a place that empowers our teams with easy-to-use tools and inspired analytics.


We are currently recruiting an Operations Lead to join the leadership team of our Digital & Data team and reporting to the Vice-President Digital & Data. This role will work with our Data Engineers, Data Analysts and Data Scientists to drive the delivery of the highest-priority projects in Data & Analytics, serving as a point person for our teams most critical deliverables. This role is also a key contributor to the Digital & Data strategy, supporting the Digital & Data leadership team to drive strategic priorities at pace. If you are a motivated and collaborative individual with a passion for agile methodologies and data-driven decision making, this role is for you!


JOB RESPONSIBILITIES:

  • Act as a coach to the Data & Analytics delivery teams, by demonstrating Agile ceremonies including sprint planning, daily stand-ups, sprint reviews, and retrospectives for select Data & Analytics projects and coaching delivery leads to hold Agile ceremonies in their own teams
  • Provide guidance and support to team members on Agile principles and practices, helping them to continuously improve their processes and deliverables.
  • Foster a collaborative and inclusive team environment, ensuring that team members have the necessary resources, tools, and information to achieve their goals.
  • Help the team to identify and remove any obstacles or impediments that may affect their progress or productivity, including data-related challenges, technical dependencies, and stakeholder engagement.
  • Collaborate with product owners, data stakeholders, and business partners in our digital & data teams to ensure that Product Owners in data and analytics are properly refining and prioritizing their backlogs, and that sprint goals are aligned with business objectives.
  • Monitor and track team progress and performance using Agile metrics, and provide regular status updates to stakeholders and leadership.
  • Encourage a culture of continuous improvement and innovation, and facilitate knowledge sharing and learning across the team.
  • Stay up-to-date with Agile best practices and industry trends, and proactively identify opportunities to optimize Agile processes and methodologies within the Data & Analytics team.


KEY QUALIFICATION & EXPERIENCES:

  • Bachelor's degree in a relevant field, such as Data Science, Computer Science, or related field, or equivalent work experience.
  • At least 3 years of prior experience in Consulting, or Project Management
  • Proven experience working as a Project Manager or Operations Lead in an Agile, technology delivery environment, preferably with data and analytics teams (Scrum master certification preferred)
  • Excellent facilitation, coaching, and mentoring skills, with the ability to build relationships and communicate effectively with cross-functional teams.
  • Familiarity with data technologies, tools, and processes, such as data engineering, data science, data visualization, and analytics. (Azure stack preferred)
  • Understanding of the role and importance of Data Governance practice to effective Data Analytics.
  • Demonstrated ability to identify and address team dynamics, conflicts, and challenges in a constructive manner.
  • Experience with Agile tools such as Azure DevOps or Jira
  • Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to think critically and strategically, with a data-driven mindset.
  • Self-motivated and able to work independently, with a proactive and results-oriented mindset.
  • Ability to adapt to changing priorities and work in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.


The above information indicates the general nature and level of work performed by employees within this classification. It is not a comprehensive inventory of all duties, responsibilities and qualifications required of employees assigned to this job.

McCain Foods is an equal opportunity employer. We see value in ensuring we have a diverse, antiracist, inclusive, merit-based, and equitable workplace. As a global family-owned company we are proud to reflect the diverse communities around the world in which we live and work. We recognize that diversity drives our creativity, resilience, and success and makes our business stronger.

McCain is an accessible employer. If you require an accommodation throughout the recruitment process (including alternate formats of materials or accessible meeting rooms), please let us know and we will work with you to meet your needs.

The health and safety of McCain employees and their families has been our number one priority since the start of COVID-19 pandemic. With vaccination restrictions easing across the globe we do not currently require employees to be vaccinated, but we reserve the right to change this mandate in line with health guidance and regulations in each country.

Your privacy is important to us. By submitting personal data or information to us, you agree this will be handled in accordance with the Global Privacy Policy

cover_letter:
Dear Hiring Manager,

As a full-stack data scientist with expertise in machine learning, programming, and data visualization, I am excited to apply for the role of Data & Analytics Operations Lead at McCain Foods. I am confident in my ability to support the Digital & Data team's strategic priorities in driving the delivery of critical data & analytics projects effectively.

I was thrilled to hear of McCain's ambitious digital transformation and commitment to implementing regenerative agriculture practices. I firmly believe that technology can drive innovation and growth while also furthering sustainability efforts. Your mission resonates with my desire to work in an industry that truly makes a positive impact.

In my previous role as a data scientist, I helped my team analyze sentiments, classify interests, extract keywords, and reduce production costs by 50% by building models trained with GPT-2. Furthermore, I implemented agile methodologies and ceremonies while fostering collaborative and inclusive team environments that drove productivity. I believe these experiences provide strong evidence of my qualifications for the role of Data & Analytics Operations Lead.

I understand that data-related challenges and stakeholder engagement can sometimes be a hurdle in moving forward with digital projects. As an AI developer intern, I crawled through multiple websites and implemented computer vision techniques in diagnosing Parkinson's disease from MRI scans. In helping to raise awareness by easily accessible technology, and in my other projects, I have honed my ability to work collaboratively across disciplines to drive the efficient and effective delivery of critical projects.

I would be thrilled to contribute my skills and experience to McCain Foods' digital transformation and sustainability efforts. Thank you for your time and consideration. I look forward to discussing my qualifications in further detail.

Best regards,

Geoffrey Wong

dir="ltr"><div>
 Worker Type: Employee
 <div></div> Group: Workforce Analytics & Strategic Planning Department
 <div></div> Job Post End Date: 05/30/2023
 <div></div>
 <div>
   About this opportunity:
 </div>
 <div>
   The Workforce Analytics & Strategic Planning team in Human Resources (HR) is looking for an individual who is passionate about turning data into meaningful information, themes and insights that can be easily understood and applied across HR and Cenovus. Working closely with the Centers of Excellence (COEs) and the business, the Workforce Analytics & Reporting team strives to understand the needs of its partners in order to improve the value from data, reporting and analytics. Through this collaboration, the Workforce Analytics & Reporting team helps to develop insight that may drive action and provides advisory services in support of strategic objectives within HR and across Cenovus.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
   The successful candidates responsibilities will include activities associated with developing predictive models to identify solutions for workforce related organizational challenges, discovering valuable insights and opportunities using statistical analysis, data mining and algorithmic techniques, and using visualization tools to build and maintaining dashboards, metrics and scorecards. The position requires a combination of technical, business and communication skills, with a focus on discovering, interpreting and communicating meaningful patterns and insights to advise strategic decision making in alignment with Cenovus business and people strategies. The role will work closely with teams across HR and the business.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
   About Cenovus:
 </div>
 <div>
   Were a Canadian-based integrated energy company headquartered in Calgary. Were committed to maximizing value by sustainably developing our assets in a safe, innovative and cost-efficient manner, integrating environmental, social and governance considerations into our business plans.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
   We operate in Canada, the United States and the Asia Pacific region. Our operations include oil sands projects in northern Alberta, thermal and conventional crude oil and natural gas projects across Western Canada, crude oil production offshore Newfoundland and Labrador and natural gas and liquids production offshore China and Indonesia. Cenovuss downstream operations include upgrading, refining and marketing operations in Canada and the United States.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
   Our shares trade under the symbol CVE, and are listed on the Toronto and New York stock exchanges.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
   For more information, visit 
  <div>
   cenovus.com
  </div>.
 </div>
 <div>
   Find Cenovus on 
  <div>
   Facebook
  </div>, 
  <div>
   Twitter
  </div>, 
  <div>
   LinkedIn
  </div>, 
  <div>
   YouTube
  </div> and 
  <div>
   Instagram
  </div>.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
   Why we work at Cenovus:
 </div>
 <ul>
  <li> Safety as a core value</li>
  <li> Competitive compensation</li>
  <li> Flex time</li>
  <li> Employer paid benefits: health, dental, vision & more</li>
  <li> Volunteering opportunities</li>
  <li> Community Investment activities</li>
  <li> Inclusive work environment</li>
  <li> Career progression/internal mobility opportunities</li>
  <li> Company/team building events</li>
 </ul>
 <div></div>
 <div>
   Responsibilities:
 </div>
 <ul>
  <li> Develop and implement the people analytics strategy within HR and deliver impactful analysis that advises decision making to leaders within HR and across Cenovus</li>
  <li> Support the visualization of workforce analytics, including demographics, statistics, metrics, and benchmarking on an on-going basis</li>
  <li> Translate business requirements into effective data visualization dashboards (charts, graphs and illustrations) to ensure effective stories are told with the data</li>
  <li> Champion the identification, development and execution of HR metrics and key performance indicators to evaluate the efficiency, effectiveness and impact of HR programs, processes and systems</li>
  <li> Implement predictive analytics through data models and the deployment of statistical analyses, cause-and-effect hypothesis testing, and scenario planning</li>
  <li> Deliver practical, concrete, and proactive analytics that drive HRs forecasting capabilities, business insights, and effective evaluation of Cenovuss investment in human capital through HR programs and services</li>
  <li> Develop creative ways to streamline, improve and automate processes</li>
  <li> Engage in project work to help mature HR business processes to enable the collection of high-quality data</li>
  <li> Provide thought leadership on analytics that leads to continuous improvement of the Workforce Analytics program</li>
  <li> Stay connected to external trends and innovations</li>
  <li> Collaborate with HRIS and HR data owners, as well as the Cenovus Data Office, to promote appropriate data governance, processes, policies and stewardship</li>
  <li> Build and maintain collaborative relationships with team members at various levels across the organization</li>
  <li> Provide training and support to end users to support self-serve visualizations and analytics</li>
 </ul>
 <div></div>
 <div>
   Qualifications:
 </div>
 <ul>
  <li> Must be legally entitled to work in Canada</li>
  <li> Post-secondary degree in Business, Computer Science, Statistics or related fields</li>
  <li> 7+ years of experience manipulating large datasets and using databases</li>
  <li> Shown experience in data analysis and data science</li>
  <li> Strong leadership and interpersonal skills</li>
  <li> Proven experience with data analytics concepts and standard processes</li>
  <li> Strong quantitative and analytical skills, with sophisticated understanding of analytics tools and languages such as Power BI, R, Python and Excel VBA</li>
  <li> Strong data expertise, including a solid understanding of data architecture, modeling, transformation, governance and management skills</li>
  <li> Natural tendency to validate data results to ensure accuracy in data and reporting; interested in investigating anomalies independently</li>
  <li> Ability to convey ideas and data clearly and effectively in written and verbal communications across all levels of the organization</li>
  <li> Demonstrated experience in identifying continuous improvement opportunities</li>
  <li> Demonstrated passion for learning and challenging the status quo</li>
  <li> Attitude focused on creativity, innovation and problem-solving</li>
  <li> Ability to work independently, multi-task and handle contending priorities effectively</li>
  <li> Ability to maintain a high degree of confidentiality</li>
  <li> Self-motivated, creative problem solver with the ability to arrive at solutions independently</li>
  <li> Demonstrated ability to translate data into meaningful information through visualizations and commentaries</li>
  <li> Demonstrated track record of handling with highly sensitive data, and exercising proven judgement and discretion</li>
 </ul>
 <div></div>
 <div>
   At Cenovus we embrace diversity of thought, experience and backgrounds to help us make better business decisions, address our challenges, seize opportunities and unlock innovative solutions. We define diversity as the variety of people, including all of the unique attributes of our staff, as well as the variety of ideas within our organization. Building an inclusive workplace by drawing on the skills and talents of a diverse workforce provides Cenovus with a competitive advantage. We believe its important to maximize the potential of everyone who works for our company and ensure people feel respected, appreciated and heard. We define inclusion as diversity in action, creating an environment of involvement, respect and connection, where various ideas, backgrounds and perspectives are harnessed to create business value.
 </div>

Full Job Description
Worker Type: Employee Group: Workforce Analytics & Strategic Planning Department Job Post End Date: 05/30/2023
About this opportunity:
The Workforce Analytics & Strategic Planning team in Human Resources (HR) is looking for an individual who is passionate about turning data into meaningful information, themes and insights that can be easily understood and applied across HR and Cenovus. Working closely with the Centers of Excellence (COEs) and the business, the Workforce Analytics & Reporting team strives to understand the needs of its partners in order to improve the value from data, reporting and analytics. Through this collaboration, the Workforce Analytics & Reporting team helps to develop insight that may drive action and provides advisory services in support of strategic objectives within HR and across Cenovus.
The successful candidates responsibilities will include activities associated with developing predictive models to identify solutions for workforce related organizational challenges, discovering valuable insights and opportunities using statistical analysis, data mining and algorithmic techniques, and using visualization tools to build and maintaining dashboards, metrics and scorecards. The position requires a combination of technical, business and communication skills, with a focus on discovering, interpreting and communicating meaningful patterns and insights to advise strategic decision making in alignment with Cenovus business and people strategies. The role will work closely with teams across HR and the business.
About Cenovus:
Were a Canadian-based integrated energy company headquartered in Calgary. Were committed to maximizing value by sustainably developing our assets in a safe, innovative and cost-efficient manner, integrating environmental, social and governance considerations into our business plans.
We operate in Canada, the United States and the Asia Pacific region. Our operations include oil sands projects in northern Alberta, thermal and conventional crude oil and natural gas projects across Western Canada, crude oil production offshore Newfoundland and Labrador and natural gas and liquids production offshore China and Indonesia. Cenovuss downstream operations include upgrading, refining and marketing operations in Canada and the United States.
Our shares trade under the symbol CVE, and are listed on the Toronto and New York stock exchanges.
For more information, visit
cenovus.com.
Find Cenovus onFacebook,Twitter,LinkedIn,Instagram.
YouTubeand
Why we work at Cenovus:
- Safety as a core value
- Competitive compensation
- Flex time
- Employer paid benefits: health, dental, vision & more
- Volunteering opportunities
- Community Investment activities
- Inclusive work environment
- Career progression/internal mobility opportunities
- Company/team building events
Responsibilities:
- Develop and implement the people analytics strategy within HR and deliver impactful analysis that advises decision making to leaders within HR and across Cenovus
- Support the visualization of workforce analytics, including demographics, statistics, metrics, and benchmarking on an on-going basis
- Translate business requirements into effective data visualization dashboards (charts, graphs and illustrations) to ensure effective stories are told with the data
- Champion the identification, development and execution of HR metrics and key performance indicators to evaluate the efficiency, effectiveness and impact of HR programs, processes and systems
- Implement predictive analytics through data models and the deployment of statistical analyses, cause-and-effect hypothesis testing, and scenario planning
- Deliver practical, concrete, and proactive analytics that drive HRs forecasting capabilities, business insights, and effective evaluation of Cenovuss investment in human capital through HR programs and services
- Develop creative ways to streamline, improve and automate processes
- Engage in project work to help mature HR business processes to enable the collection of high-quality data
- Provide thought leadership on analytics that leads to continuous improvement of the Workforce Analytics program
- Stay connected to external trends and innovations
- Collaborate with HRIS and HR data owners, as well as the Cenovus Data Office, to promote appropriate data governance, processes, policies and stewardship
- Build and maintain collaborative relationships with team members at various levels across the organization
- Provide training and support to end users to support self-serve visualizations and analytics
Qualifications:
- Must be legally entitled to work in Canada
- Post-secondary degree in Business, Computer Science, Statistics or related fields
- 7+ years of experience manipulating large datasets and using databases
- Shown experience in data analysis and data science
- Strong leadership and interpersonal skills
- Proven experience with data analytics concepts and standard processes
- Strong quantitative and analytical skills, with sophisticated understanding of analytics tools and languages such as Power BI, R, Python and Excel VBA
- Strong data expertise, including a solid understanding of data architecture, modeling, transformation, governance and management skills
- Natural tendency to validate data results to ensure accuracy in data and reporting; interested in investigating anomalies independently
- Ability to convey ideas and data clearly and effectively in written and verbal communications across all levels of the organization
- Demonstrated experience in identifying continuous improvement opportunities
- Demonstrated passion for learning and challenging the status quo
- Attitude focused on creativity, innovation and problem-solving
- Ability to work independently, multi-task and handle contending priorities effectively
- Ability to maintain a high degree of confidentiality
- Self-motivated, creative problem solver with the ability to arrive at solutions independently
- Demonstrated ability to translate data into meaningful information through visualizations and commentaries
- Demonstrated track record of handling with highly sensitive data, and exercising proven judgement and discretion
At Cenovus we embrace diversity of thought, experience and backgrounds to help us make better business decisions, address our challenges, seize opportunities and unlock innovative solutions. We define diversity as the variety of people, including all of the unique attributes of our staff, as well as the variety of ideas within our organization. Building an inclusive workplace by drawing on the skills and talents of a diverse workforce provides Cenovus with a competitive advantage. We believe its important to maximize the potential of everyone who works for our company and ensure people feel respected, appreciated and heard. We define inclusion as diversity in action, creating an environment of involvement, respect and connection, where various ideas, backgrounds and perspectives are harnessed to create business value.
If you require accessibility assistance to complete the on-line application or otherwise apply for an open position with Cenovus, its subsidiaries and affiliates, please email
careeropportunities@cenovus.com.
Note: The application deadline for this position is 11:59 PM MT May 29, 2023.
This posting represents the desired scope, accountabilities, skills and experience requirements of the job. These requirements may be modified to support business needs. Title and compensation administration will be based on the skills and capabilities of the successful incumbent.
Notification
To be considered for a position, please click Apply and create an account or sign in to your Cenovus Careers profile.
Immediately following successful submission of your online application, you will receive an online notification confirming Cenovus's receipt of your resume.
Only those applicants who apply directly to a posted position and are selected for an interview will be contacted. We will not accept agency or third-party candidate submissions.
To follow the status of your application, log in to your Cenovus Careers profile and click on the appropriate job under My Applications.

cover_letter:
Dear Hiring Manager,

I am writing to express my interest in the Manager, Workforce Analytics & Reporting role at Cenovus. As a full-stack data scientist with a strong passion for turning data into meaningful insights, I believe I am highly qualified for this position, and my experience aligns with your company's purpose of incorporating environmental, social, and governance considerations into business plans.

I am impressed by the diverse range of responsibilities outlined in the job description and am eager to contribute to such significant project work. As shown in my experience as a data scientist at Hotmob Limited, I built a generator that converted 2D images into 3D models and crawled online websites to provide insights into consumer behavior patterns. Additionally, while working at Cenovus, I can bring value in effectively communicating, analyzing, and visualizing data trends with stakeholders across HR and Cenovus by using visualization tools like PowerBI, Tableau, Looker Studio, and incorporating standard processes of data analytics like using R, Python, and other frameworks.

I have also noticed Cenovus has an interest in identifying continuous improvement opportunities and developing creative ways to streamline and automate processes. In this regard, I would like to mention that I invented a molecular toxicity classifier with an 87% accuracy that significantly reduced the duration of the data categorization process and increased the presence of data across all medium types.

I am excited about the prospect of joining such a dynamic team and contributing my skills and expertise to Cenovus's growing workforce. Thank you for considering my application for this opportunity.

Sincerely,

Geoffrey Wong
